Package com.intellij.openapi.editor.impl.softwrap

Class SoftWrapsStorage

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.openapi.editor.impl.softwrap.SoftWrapsStorage
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Dumpable

    public class SoftWrapsStorage
extends java.lang.Object
implements Dumpable
    Holds registered soft wraps and provides monitoring and management facilities for them.

    Not thread-safe.

      • getSoftWrapIndex

        public int getSoftWrapIndex(int offset)
        Tries to find index of the target soft wrap stored at myWraps collection. 'Target' soft wrap is the one that starts at the given offset.
        Parameters:
        offset - target offset
        Returns:
        index that conforms to Collections.binarySearch(List, Object) contract, i.e. non-negative returned index points to soft wrap that starts at the given offset; '-(negative value) - 1' points to position at myWraps collection where soft wrap for the given index should be inserted

      • getNumberOfSoftWrapsInRange

        Allows to answer how many soft wraps which start offsets belong to given [start; end] interval are registered withing the current storage.
        Parameters:
        startOffset - target start offset (inclusive)
        endOffset - target end offset (inclusive)
        Returns:
        number of soft wraps which start offsets belong to the target range

      • addAll

        public void addAll(java.util.List<? extends SoftWrapImpl> softWraps)
        Adds soft wraps to storage. They are supposed to be sorted by their offsets, and have offsets larger than offsets for soft wraps existing in storage at the moment.
